shows.title: (Dis)Honesty: The Truth About Lies
shows.overview: Behavioural scientist Dan Ariely discovers the complicated truth behind what happens when we lie to each other.

shows.title: 16 Acres
shows.overview: Interests collide at Ground Zero in the decade following 9/11.

shows.title: 1994: The Bloody Miracle
shows.overview: When South Africa celebrated its democracy in 1994, many believed that civil war was inevitable.

shows.title: 20/20 Presents Black Panther: In Search of Wakanda
shows.overview: ABC News Studios partners with Rock’n Robin Productions for “20/20 Presents Black Panther: In Search of Wakanda,” the one-hour program hosted by “Good Morning America” co-anchor Robin Roberts exploring the evolution of Black Panther from the comic emerging in the 1960s to the film the world fell in love with in 2018. Roberts sits down with director Ryan Coogler to discuss the highly anticipated sequel to the Marvel Studios’ phenomenon, “Black Panther,” and how the film honors the legacy of Chadwick Boseman. EGOT winner and moderator of “The View,” Whoopi Goldberg, exclusively interviews Boseman’s widow, Simone Ledward Boseman. In homage to King T’Challa and one week in advance of the film’s premiere, the program features an exclusive sneak peek of “Black Panther: Wakanda Forever.”
shows.originalTitle: 20/20 Presents Black Panther: In Search of Wakanda

shows.title: A Fragile Trust: Plagiarism, Power, and Jayson Blair at the New York Times
shows.originalTitle: A Fragile Trust: Plagiarism, Power, and Jayson Blair at the New York Times

shows.title: A People Without A Land
shows.overview: Settlement expansion across Palestine is out of control. Is the patchwork of remaining Palestinian land now so fragmented it could never form a viable future state? This incisive film explores the question of whether Israeli settlers have destroyed all hope of return for the villages' original occupants and asks if the One State Solution is doomed beyond hope of being salvaged.

shows.title: A Sexplanation
shows.overview: A 36-year-old health reporter's quest for better sex education uncovers naked truths as he unlearns the sexual shame he grew up with. From neuroscience labs to church, conversations with experts lead to a happier, healthier, sexier future.

shows.title: After Uvalde: Guns, Grief & Texas Politics
shows.overview: A year after the Uvalde school shooting, the community’s trauma and the fight over assault rifles. With the Texas Tribune, journalist Maria Hinojosa examines the police response, Uvalde’s history of struggle and its efforts to heal.
shows.originalTitle: After Uvalde: Guns, Grief & Texas Politics

shows.title: Against the Tide
shows.overview: A Showtime Sports chronicle of the seminal 1970 college football matchup between Alabama's Crimson Tide and USC Trojans at Birmingham's Legion Field. Through interviews with former Alabama legends Joe Namath, John Mitchell and USC stars Sam "Bam" Cunningham, Jimmy Jones and more, this documentary examines coach Paul "Bear" Bryant's surprising decision to bring a dominant, racially integrated football team onto the field in Birmingham for the very first time and reveals the impact college football played in the struggle for integration.

shows.title: Age of Easy Money
shows.overview: The role of the Federal Reserve’s “easy money” policies in the current economic uncertainty. From the Great Recession to the rise in inflation, the ongoing fragility of the financial system and the widening gap between Wall St. and Main St.

shows.title: Alec Baldwin: Unscripted
shows.overview: The actor sat down for an exclusive interview with George Stephanopoulos, produced by George Stephanopoulos Productions, his first since the deadly shooting on the set of his movie, 'Rust'

shows.title: Alien Boy: The Life and Death of James Chasse
shows.overview: This revealing doc centers on one man's struggle with schizophrenia, and contemplates the actions of the police officers responsible for his death.

shows.title: Alive Inside
shows.overview: El fundador de una organización, lucha contra un sistema de salud para demostrar la utilidad de la música en la lucha contra la pérdida de memoria.

shows.title: Amazon Empire: The Rise and Reign of Jeff Bezos
shows.overview: Examine Amazon CEO Jeff Bezos' ascent to power and the global impact of the empire he built. The film also investigates the darker side of the company's rapid growth, and the challenge of trying to rein in the power of the richest man in the world.
shows.originalTitle: Amazon Empire: The Rise and Reign of Jeff Bezos

shows.title: America's Dangerous Trucks
shows.overview: Deadly truck accidents and the fight over measures that could save thousands of lives. With ProPublica, investigating decades of legal maneuvering, political influence, lax regulation and industry opposition, as deaths rise.

shows.title: American Autumn: An Occudoc
shows.overview: This film explores the Occupy movement and its demand for a system that places social and economic justice above corporate greed.

shows.title: American Coup
shows.overview: The inside and untold story of the 1953 CIA-backed coup in Iran that toppled the democratically elected Prime Minister Mohammad Mossadegh. Known as `Operation Ajax', this covert operation would be the first overthrow of a foreign government by the agency, and serve as a template for all future CIA coups.

shows.title: American Winter
shows.overview: Families struggle in the aftermath of the worst economic crisis since the Great Depression.

shows.title: Atlantic
shows.overview: Narrated by actor Brendan Gleeson, this documentary follows the fortunes of three small fishing communities and the global resources they depend on.
